The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 March is 41,065 (4,753 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 March, there were 292 new confirmed cases (33.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 March, there were 298 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (6 fewer cases).
